    "inputs" : {
    
    
    "category" :
    
    
    "Information"
    ,
    
    "consequences" : [
    
    
    
    "The components (with the exception of the electric air-conditioning compressor) are always flushed against the direction of flow of refrigerant in the air conditioning system."
    ,
    
    
    "The filter in the flushing device for refrigerant circuits must be changed after 5 to 10 flushing cycles (flushed vehicles), depending on the type and extent of contamination of the flushed refrigerant circuits. If a highly contaminated refrigerant circuit is flushed (the refrigerant machine oil from the refrigerant circuit is black and viscous or there are a lot of chips in the refrigerant circuit), the filter must be changed after flushing this refrigerant circuit. If a refrigerant circuit is highly contaminated like this, it is also a good idea to flush the refrigerant circuit again after changing the filter."
    
    ]
    
    }
    
